{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"badb212c-43f5-4cc9-a0d9-51b1c9f22870","content":"Analyzing crash dumps is outside the scope of the `dump-collect` skill (which is for **collecting** dumps, not analyzing them). However, here's how you can analyze your `.dmp` file:\n\n**Using `dotnet-dump analyze`** (cross-platform):\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\ndotnet-dump analyze your-file.dmp\n```\nUseful SOS commands inside the analyzer:\n| Command | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `clrstack` | Managed call stack |\n| `pe` | Print last exception |\n| `dumpheap -stat` | Heap summary |\n| `threads` | List all threads |\n| `clrthreads` | Managed thread info |\n\n**Using Visual Studio** (Windows): Just open the `.dmp` file and click **\"Debug with Managed Only\"**.\n\n**Using `lldb`** (Linux/macOS):\n```bash\nlldb --core your-file.dmp\nplugin load libsosplugin.so\nclrstack\npe\n```\n\nStart with `pe` (print exception) — it usually points straight to the root cause. Would you like help with any of these steps?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"08601028-6326-4e6f-ad5c-85e9eec4d1ff","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about analyzing a .dmp crash dump file. Let me check the available skills - there's a `dump-collect` skill, but its description specifically says:\n\n- USE FOR: enabling automatic crash dumps, capturing dumps, setting up dump collection\n- DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze\n\nSo the skill is not appropriate here. I should help the user directly with guidance on analyzing crash dumps.","outputTokens":400,"requestId":"7651:2FE433:E4F89A:10CE636:69FE93A4"},"id":"103d0c90-92da-438f-9e90-e35678bd3c3c","timestamp":"2026-05-09T01:53:51.568Z","parentId":"7af5f6f6-b934-44f6-8218-71ce4c9b90a2"}
